headline: Apple upgraded, AMD downgraded: Wall Street’s top analyst calls
summary: The most talked about and market moving research calls around Wall Street are now in one place. Here are today’s research calls that investors need to know, as compiled by The Fly. Top Upgrades: MoffettNathanson upgraded Apple (AAPL) to Neutral from Sell with a $225 price target. A number of key headwinds have faded and the “worst-case scenarios are off the table,” the firm tells investors. Evercore ISI upgraded Brinker (EAT) to Outperform from In Line with a price target of $210, up from $190.
